    "title": "Spirit Glyph",
    "description": "&quot;There are as many types of motion or change as there are meanings of the word 'is'.&quot;\n– Aristotle, 'Physics'.\n\n&quot;I have bought this wonderful machine- a computer. Now I am rather an authority on gods, so I identified the machine- it seems to me to be an Old Testament god with a lot of rules and no mercy.&quot;\n– Joseph Campbell, 'The Power of Myth' (1988).\n\n&quot;A young man who had been troubling society with impalpable doctrines of a new civilization which he called 'the Kingdom of Heaven' had been put out of the way; and I can imagine that believer in material power murmuring as he went homeward, 'it will all blow over now.' Yes. The wind from the Kingdom of Heaven has blown over the world, and shall blow for centuries yet.&quot;\n– George William Russell, in 'The Economics of Ireland and the Policy of the British Government' (1921), p. 23.",
